{{Infobox Artwork | image_file = Konstantin Makovsky - Christmastide Divination.jpg | image_size = 300px | title = Christmastide Divination | artist = [[Konstantin Makovsky]] | year = {{circa|1905}} | medium = [[Oil on canvas]] | height_metric = 160 | width_metric = 232 | height_imperial = | width_imperial = | metric_unit = cm | imperial_unit = in | city = [[Saint Petersburg]] | museum = [[State Museum of the History of Religion]] }} '''''Christmastide Divination''''' ({{lang-ru|"Святочное гадание"}}) is a painting by Russian artist [[Konstantin Makovsky]] from around 1905. The painting shows a moonlit Russian folk divination during [[Eastern Orthodox]] [[Christmastide]] (''svyatki'') in a rural [[log house]] (''[[izba]]''). Five out of seven depicted women gathered around a [[rooster]] pecking the grain, the [[alectryomancy]] which foretells a marriage in the near future.<ref name="culture">{{cite web | url =http://vm1.culture.ru/muzey_istorii_religii/catalog/small/0002500424/|title=Картина "Святочное гадание"|publisher=Vm1.culture.ru| language=Russian| accessdate =13 January 2016}}</ref> The girls count the grains pecked by the rooster, watching if he did not peck more than twelve.<ref name="hp">{{cite web | url =http://www.hudojnik-peredvijnik.ru/makovskij-k-e/makovskij-k-e-svyatochnye-gadaniya/|title=Маковский К.Е. "Святочные гадания". Описание картины|publisher=Hudojnik-peredvijnik.ru| language=Russian| accessdate =13 January 2016}}</ref> If the number of remaining grains would be even, then the marriage will happen soon, and if odd, then it will be in the next year.<ref name="hp"/> A sleeping elder woman is depicted sitting on a bench to the left. The upper left part of the painting shows a candlelit [[icon corner]].
