{{Infobox collection | name = The World of Anna Sui | image = | image_caption = | housed_at = The [[Fashion and Textile Museum]]<ref name="BLANKSonWAS">{{cite web |url=https://www.businessoffashion.com/articles/opinion/anna-sui-exhibit-fashion-textile-museum |title=Weaving Through the World of Anna Sui |last= |first= |date=2 November 2016 |website= [[businessoffashion.com]] |access-date=23 January 2016 |quote=}}</ref> | curators = [[Dennis Nothdruft]]<ref name="CONLONonWAS">{{cite web |url=http://www.vogue.co.uk/article/anna-sui-retrospective-exhibition-the-fashion-and-textiles-museum-may-2016 |title=London To Host Anna Sui Retrospective |last=Conlon |first=Scarlett |date=2 November 2017 |website=vogue.co.uk |publisher=Vogue UK |access-date=23 January 2017 |quote=}}</ref> | funded_by = | website = http://www.ftmlondon.org/ftm-exhibitions/the-world-of-anna-sui/ }}
'''The World of Anna Sui''' was an [[exhibition]] housed at [[London]]'s [[Fashion and Textile Museum]] from 26 May to 1 October 2017.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vogue.com/13500722/anna-sui-book-by-tim-blanks-photos/ |title=Enter the Age of Anna Sui |last=Yotka |first=Steff |date=7 November 2016 |website=vogue.com |publisher=Vogue |access-date=23 January 2017 |quote=}}</ref>
The exhibition was curated by the museum's head [[curator]] [[Dennis Nothdruft]] and focused on the effect [[Anna Sui|Sui's]] work has had on the [[history of fashion design]].<ref name="FTMonASW">{{cite web |url=http://www.ftmlondon.org/ftm-exhibitions/the-world-of-anna-sui/ |title=The World of Anna Sui |last= |first= |date=2017 |website=ftmlondon.org |publisher=The Fashion and Textile Museum |access-date=23 January 2017 |quote=}}</ref> The exhibit featured over 100 looks from the Sui’s archive, spanning the entirety the designer's career from 1981 to 2017.<ref name="CONLONonWAS"/> It also marked the first time an [[American people|American]] [[fashion designer]] had been the feature of a [[retrospective]] exhibit in the [[United Kingdom]]. One key theme of the exhibition was the exploration of national identity through the medium of fashion and textiles.<ref name="CONLONonWAS"/>
